<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 2:31PM EST  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS AFTERNOON...
Patchy fog has formed across far northern Indiana and southern
Lower Michigan. The fog may be locally dense into the late
afternoon hours with localized visibilities dropping to one
quarter of a mile. Motorists should be prepared for rapid changes
in visibility due to the patchy nature of the dense fog.
Visibilities are expected to improve after 6 PM EST this evening.</description>
